Put a large #saucepan{} of water with a pinch of @salt{} on to boil for the pasta. Halve, peel and finely chop the @onion{1}(peeled and finely chopped). Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1}(roughly chopped) (stalks and all). Finely chop the @sun-dried tomatoes{30%g}(finely chopped). Halve the @red chilli{1/2}(halved lengthways, deseeded and finely chopped) lengthways, deseed and finely chop.

Heat a good glug of @oil{a good glug} in a #frying pan{} on medium heat. Once hot, add the onion. Season with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @ground black pepper{pinch}. Stir and cook until the onion is soft, about ~{5%minutes}. Add the garlic, sun-dried tomatoes and as much chilli as you dare and cook for ~{2%minutes} more.

Add the @red wine vinegar{12%ml} and allow it to evaporate, then add the @chopped tomatoes{1}(finely chopped) and a pinch of @sugar{pinch}(if you have some). Let the mixture simmer on medium-low heat until you have a nice thick sauce, about ~{10%minutes}.

Meanwhile, add the @spaghetti{180%g} to your pan of boiling water. Cook until 'al dente', ~{11%minutes}.

> 'Al dente' simply means the pasta is cooked through but has a tiny bit of firmness left in the middle.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and drizzle with a little @oil{a little} to stop it sticking together.

Once the sauce has thickened, stir in the @king prawns{150%g} and simmer for ~{3-5%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque all the way through.

Combine the pasta and sauce. Sprinkle over most of the parsley and toss everything together to mix thoroughly. Serve, sprinkled with the remaining parsley. Enjoy!